=== Etymology ===
{{ja-kanjitab-top}}
! [[形]] || [[容]] || [[動]] || [[詞]]
{{ja-kanjitab-bottom}}
[[形容]] (けいよう, ''keiyō''), "adjectival" + [[動詞]] (どうし, ''dōshi''), "verb"

===Noun===
{{janoun|けいようどうし|keiyōdōshi}}
# {{Template:ja:grammar|index=けいようどうし}} adjective; adjectival noun; (literally) "adjectival verb"; copular noun; ''na''-adjective; quasi-adjective 

====Usage notes====
{{wikipedia|Japanese adjectives}}
Japanese has three classes of words that correspond to adjectives in English: 形容動詞 (''keiyōdōshi''), [[形容詞]] (''keiyōshi''), and [[連体詞]] (''rentaishi''). There are no generally accepted English translations for the above parts of speech, and varying texts adopt different translations. Because some western texts call [[形容詞]] (''keiyōshi'') "adjectival verbs", caution must be taken when using the literal translation of 形容動詞 (''keiyōdōshi'').

